definition: to flow/to disseminate/to circulate or spread/to move or drift/to degenerate/to banish or send into exile/stream of water or sth resembling one/class, rate or grade

sentences.english: I'm just a small-time director, a new one at that.
sentences.chinese: 我只是个三流导演，一个新人。

sentences.english: Jack graduated from a third grade college.
sentences.chinese: 杰克毕业于一所三流大学。

sentences.english: That is just a third-rate company.
sentences.chinese: 那只是个三流公司而已。

sentences.english: Some say that Cockney was also used by small-time criminals to confuse the police.
sentences.chinese: 也有人说一些三流罪犯也说这种英语以骗过警察。

sentences.english: The taxi stopped in front of a shabby, third-rate hotel.
sentences.chinese: 出租车在一家破旧的三流旅馆门口停下来。

sentences.english: I fully agree. Better purchase a third class phone of indian make than investing a dollar on a china phone.
sentences.chinese: 完全同意，买三流印度手机比花钱买中国手机更好。

sentences.english: Colleges are third-rate and should be a national disgrace.
sentences.chinese: 大学是三流的，这应该成为这个国家的耻辱。

sentences.english: First-rate mingles with third-rate, that is the real situation of China's present development.
sentences.chinese: 而一流和三流交织在一起，就是中国的真实发展现状。
我认为那场演出是三流的。

sentences.english: He is nothing more than a small-time thief.
sentences.chinese: 他不过是个三流的小贼罢了。

definition: switch to a job one was not trained for
(lit.) name not encountered in the classics/unknown (person)/nobody
variant of 下三濫|下三滥[xia4 san1 lan4]
to degenerate/impoverished/to fall (into poverty)/to be reduced (to begging)
peak/apex/world best/number one/finest (competitors)/top (figures in a certain field)
